main event: A pilot in Wiesbaden, Germany spotted an illuminated colored object that appeared larger than a star, approached, and then disappeared from west to east.
interesting points: The object appeared to be bluish in color and made no sound.
The sighting lasted for approximately 30 seconds.
This report is being forwarded to Project Blue Book, which suggests it was considered an unusual sighting.
The object's movement included approaching and disappearing on the horizon.
The location of the sighting was Wiesbaden, Germany.
sighted object: An illuminated colored object that appeared larger than a star
